固相核磁共振法表征纳米物质

课程编码：41514Y 英文名称：Characterization of Nanoporous Materials 课时：16 学分：1.00 课程属性：高级强化课 主讲教师：-

教学目的要求

预修课程

教材

主要内容
Nanoporous materials are the framework materials with nanometer-sized pores and channels. They belong to one of the most important classes of nanomaterials with numerous current and potential industrial/technological applications in areas of catalysis, separation, sensors, batteries, fuel cells, and solid-state electronic/optical/magnetic/photonic devices. Characterization of nanoporous materials is very important because understanding the relationship between the novel properties of these materials and their unique structures is fundamentally important for the development of new applications and the performance improvement of their current uses. Solid-state nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) spectroscopy is one of the most powerful techniques for characterization. This course is an introduction to application of solid-state NMR in nanoporous materials (in particular micro- and mesoporous materials).

NMR spectra of solids are in general much more complicated than those of isotropic mobile solutions or liquids. In the first half of the course, an examination of why solids behave differently in the NMR experiments and how some of the problems in solids can be solved will be presented. In particular, nuclear spin interactions in solids such as shielding anisotropy, dipole-dipole coupling and quadrupolar coupling will be introduced. A number of important NMR techniques, which are used to obtain high-resolution spectra in solids will be discussed. The second part of the course will begin with a very brief overview of micro- and mesoporous materials describing the range of the materials and their applications. This will be followed by the demonstration of the power of state-of-the-art solid-state NMR techniques for solving important problems relevant to nanoporous materials through carefully chosen examples.

The presentation of materials is intended to emphasize physical concepts rather than mathematical rigor. Thus, most of the course will be descriptive in nature.

课程编码：0GX15Y 英文名称：Introduction to Confucian Thought 课时：18 学分：1.00 课程属性：公共选修课 主讲教师：-

教学目的要求

预修课程

教材

主要内容
第一章 “仁”学
1、说“仁”；2、释“仁”；3、里“仁”；4、处“仁”；5、不“仁”；
第二章 “孝”道
1、有子对孝的价值定位；2、孝的理念及其实践；3、《论语》对孝的表述；4、孝之内涵；5、孝的社会实践；6、孝之天经地义；7、《孝经》论孝；
第三章 “学”旨
1、“学”之与人生匡正；2、“学”之与人生幸福；3、“学”之哲理；
第四章 “言”析
1、切入点及意义；2、“巧言令色”分析；3、“巧言令色”之因；4、“巧言令色”应对；
第五章 “省”身
1、省身说之背景概略；2、吾日三省吾身详解；3、省身说的内容；4、正视省身；
第六章 “和”解
1、《论语》中“和”之学说；2、“和”之含义及其分析；3、“和”的客观性；4、“和”的非保守性；
